\end{align*}

To simplify the equation, we can multiply everything by $-10$ to clear the decimals:

\begin{align*}
0 &= 49t^2 - 238t + 280.
\end{align*}

Factoring out the greatest common divisor, we get:

\begin{align*}
0 &= 7(7t^2 - 34t + 40).
\end{align*}

Further simplifying, we factor the quadratic equation:

\begin{align*}
0 &= 7t^2 - 34t + 40 \\
&= (7t - 20)(t - 2).
\end{align*}

This gives us two possible values for $t$:

\begin{align*}
7t - 20 &= 0 \Rightarrow t = \frac{20}{7} \approx 2.857, \\
t - 2 &= 0 \Rightarrow t = 2.
\end{align*}

Since we are looking for the first time the projectile reaches 28 meters in height, we choose the smaller value of $t$:

\begin{align*}
\boxed{2}.
