Given $$\overrightarrow{a} = (3, 4)$$, and $$\overrightarrow{b}$$ is a unit vector.  
(1) If $$\overrightarrow{b} \parallel \overrightarrow{a}$$, find $$\overrightarrow{b}$$;  
(2) If $$\overrightarrow{b} \perp \overrightarrow{a}$$, find $$\overrightarrow{b}$$.

response:
Since $$\overrightarrow{a} = (3, 4)$$ and $$\overrightarrow{b}$$ is a unit vector, let $$\overrightarrow{b} = (x, y)$$ where $x^2 + y^2 = 1$ (1);  
(1) When $$\overrightarrow{b} \parallel \overrightarrow{a}$$, we have $3y - 4x = 0$ (2),  
Solving the system of equations (1) and (2), we get $$\begin{cases} \left.\begin{matrix}x= \frac {3}{5} \\ y= \frac {4}{5}\end{matrix}\right.\end{cases}$$ or $$\begin{cases} \left.\begin{matrix}x=- \frac {3}{5} \\ y=- \frac {4}{5}\end{matrix}\right.\end{cases}$$,  
Therefore, $$\overrightarrow{b} = \left( \frac {3}{5}, \frac {4}{5} \right)$$ or $\left( -\frac {3}{5}, -\frac {4}{5} \right)$;  
(2) When $$\overrightarrow{b} \perp \overrightarrow{a}$$, we have $3x + 4y = 0$ (3),  
Solving the system of equations (1) and (3), we get $$\begin{cases} \left.\begin{matrix}x=- \frac {4}{5} \\ y= \frac {3}{5}\end{matrix}\right.\end{cases}$$ or $$\begin{cases} \left.\begin{matrix}x= \frac {4}{5} \\ y=- \frac {3}{5}\end{matrix}\right.\end{cases}$$;  
Therefore, $$\overrightarrow{b} = \left( -\frac {4}{5}, \frac {3}{5} \right)$$ or $\left( \frac {4}{5}, -\frac {3}{5} \right)$.

For (1), the final answer is $$\boxed{\left( \frac {3}{5}, \frac {4}{5} \right) \text{ or } \left( -\frac {3}{5}, -\frac {4}{5} \right)}$$.

For (2), the final answer is $$\boxed{\left( -\frac {4}{5}, \frac {3}{5} \right) \text{ or } \left( \frac {4}{5}, -\frac {3}{5} \right)}$$.

